definition[0]: to begin happening or existing in a particular way, especially when this changes later
example[0]: The leaves start out a pale green, and later get darker.
example[1]: ‘The Star’ started out as a small weekly newspaper.
definition[1]: to begin your life or profession, or an important period of time
example[2]: When the band first started out, they played at small clubs.
example[3]: She started out as a model.
example[4]: young couples starting out on their life together
example[5]: Oliver started out at five, when it was still dark.
